|WKBSyntax: |YKBignore <name>
        ignore list
        unignore <name>
 
 
|WKBDESCRIPTION
|WKO===========
 
|YKOThis command allows you to ignore certain players' tells and emotes.
This is handy when a player (Or wizard) is bothering you and won't
leave you alone.  This command will allow you to ignore more than
one person as well.  If you decide at a later time that you want
to start talking to that person again, just |YKB'unignore <name>'|YKO,
where name is the person you want to quit ignoring. You can also
|YKB'ignore list'|YKO to see who you are ignoring.

If someone has you ignored, do not attempt to go around the ignore.
This counts in PK as well. Just leave them alone. Failure to do so
will result in punishment.
